headroom-skill
==============

This project is a portable, framework-agnostic skill that distills the
context-compression techniques from the Headroom project into a set of
agent rules and pure-Python helper scripts.

Original work: https://github.com/chopratejas/headroom
Original authors: Tejas Chopra (https://github.com/chopratejas) and
                  Headroom contributors.
Original license: Apache License 2.0

The compression algorithms and design patterns in this skill were
studied from the Headroom source tree (crates/headroom-core/src/transforms/,
wiki/, and docs/). The Python scripts in this repository are independent
re-implementations that use only the Python 3 standard library. They do
not import, link to, or distribute any code from the Headroom project.

